<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-6115] TaskManager should be type aware</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-6115</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, in &lt;tt&gt;TaskManager&lt;/tt&gt; we don&apos;t distinguish between &lt;tt&gt;StreamTask&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;StandbyTask&lt;/tt&gt;. However, both have quite different live cycles and thus we should try do distinguish between both.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This also affect interface &lt;tt&gt;Task&lt;/tt&gt; that should only contain method we need for both type of tasks, but not contain sub type specific methods.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
